org.opendaylight.yang.gen.v1.urn.onf.core.network.module.rev160630.g_forwardingconstruct

Interface FcSpec

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.opendaylight.yangtools.yang.binding.Augmentable<FcSpec>, org.opendaylight.yangtools.yang.binding.ChildOf<GForwardingConstruct>, org.opendaylight.yangtools.yang.binding.DataContainer, org.opendaylight.yangtools.yang.binding.DataObject, GFcSpec

    public interface FcSpec
extends org.opendaylight.yangtools.yang.binding.ChildOf<GForwardingConstruct>, org.opendaylight.yangtools.yang.binding.Augmentable<FcSpec>, GFcSpec
    References the specification that describes the capability and internal structure of of the FC(e.g. The arrangement of switches for a particular instance is described by a referencedFcSpec). The specification allows interpretation of FcPort role and switch configurations etc.

    This class represents the following YANG schema fragment defined in module onf-core-network-module 

     container fcSpec {
     leaf uuid {
         type string;
     }
     list fcPortSpec {
         key "uuid"
         leaf uuid {
             type string;
         }
         list ingressFcPortSet {
             key "topology" 
         "node" 
         "tp"
             leaf topology {
                 type topology-ref;
             }
             leaf node {
                 type node-ref;
             }
             leaf tp {
                 type tp-ref;
             }
             uses ltp-ref;
         }
         list egressFcPortSet {
             key "topology" 
         "node" 
         "tp"
             leaf topology {
                 type topology-ref;
             }
             leaf node {
                 type node-ref;
             }
             leaf tp {
                 type tp-ref;
             }
             uses ltp-ref;
         }
         leaf role {
             type role;
         }
         uses G_FcPortSetSpec;
     }
     uses G_FcSpec;
 }
    The schema path to identify an instance is onf-core-network-module/G_ForwardingConstruct/fcSpec

    To create instances of this class use FcSpecBuilder.

    See Also:
    FcSpecBuilder
